         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">30/6/88. ¶  ¶ When I sent to you, dear Mr Ridley, the two orchids, ¶ See M to H. Ridley, 29 March 1888. ¶  ¶ I had ¶  ¶ not ¶  ¶ examined them analytically, and thus - as you are well aware -, a plant...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.06.30</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Ridley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Archives, Miscellaneous correspondence.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">30/6/88.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When I sent to you, dear Mr Ridley, the two orchids,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to H. Ridley, 29 March 1888.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I had<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>examined them analytically, and thus - as you are well aware -, a plant of this kind at mere external sight might easily be placed into a wrong genus. You will be aware, how severely we are all<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">extra</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>taxed for the Centennial Exhibition, all the more so as this great event becomes at a rather sudden decision celebrated in Melbourne and not in Sydney.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Melbourne International Exhibition, 1888-9.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Until the heavy Commissioners and Jurors work will have come to an end in February, I shall not be able to work to any extent on plants descriptively, because as the head of a professional Department I am required to give every possible aid and help to the Exhibition.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thus now also I send a few Orchids, recently obtained in poor Mr Hartmann's collection. He fell victim to the clime of New Guinea; so this gathering is his Swan-song, and I should like therefore, that his name be identified with the Oberonia, should on careful examination it prove new.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The only eponymous orchids celebrating Carl Hartmann are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Sarcochilus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">har</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">t</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">mannii</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>named by M in B74.10.01, p. 248, and its synonym<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Thrixspermum hartmanni</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>described by H. G. Reichenbach in 1877 (IPNI, APNI, accessed 26 September 2023).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The trifling lot sent is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he gathered of Orchideae, nothing being kept here.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will send his ferns by post half to Mr Carruthers, half to Kew. A<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fragment</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of each might be returned to me. As Mr Baker knows, that Mr Carruthers works on Mr Forbes's ferns,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M suggested that Carruthers took responsibility for working up the ferns in Henry Forbes' British New Guinea collections when the responsibilities for description and enumeration of the collection were agreed;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see M to E. Strickland, 10 October 1885. and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to W. Carruthers,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>21 October 1885<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 95-10-21a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>doubtless the naming of those from Mr Hartmann will be left with your Chief.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What a glorious festival that of the Linnéans!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The centenary of the founding of the Linnean Society of London; see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>12 May 1888, p. 594. A full account is given in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Proceedings of the Linnean Society of London</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>1887-88, not published until May 1890 (Gage &amp; Stearn (1988), p. 218).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Oberonia<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Orchideae</p>
         </div>
